# Select only numeric columns for RSD calculation
intensity_cols <- c18_lipids %>% select(where(is.numeric)) %>% colnames()

c18_lipids <- c18_lipids %>%
  rowwise() %>%
  mutate(
    median_cv = {
      values = c_across(all_of(intensity_cols))  # only numeric columns
      if(all(is.na(values)) || mean(values, na.rm = TRUE) == 0) {
        NA_real_
      } else {
        sd(values, na.rm = TRUE) / mean(values, na.rm = TRUE)
      }
    }
  ) %>%
  ungroup()
# Identify numeric columns
numeric_cols <- c18_lipids %>%

library(readr)
library(dplyr)
library(matrixStats)
## 
## Attaching package: 'matrixStats'
## The following object is masked from 'package:dplyr':
## 
##     count
# -----------------------------
# 2. Prepare intensity matrix
# -----------------------------
# Identify intensity columns (starts with "sd_")
intensity_cols <- grep("^sd_", colnames(processed), value = TRUE)

# Extract as numeric matrix
X <- as.matrix(processed[, intensity_cols])
rownames(X) <- processed$lm_id  # optional: feature IDs

# -----------------------------
# 3. Filter out features with near-constant intensity
# -----------------------------
feature_var <- rowVars(X, na.rm = TRUE)
keep_features <- feature_var > 1e-6
X <- X[keep_features, , drop = FALSE]

# -----------------------------
# 4. Standardize X and PFAS
# -----------------------------
# Ensure your intensity matrix is features x samples
X <- as.matrix(processed[, intensity_cols])
rownames(X) <- processed$lm_id  # optional

# Make sure pfas_df rows match the intensity columns
pfas_df <- pfas_df[match(intensity_cols, pfas_df$sample_id), ]
## Warning: Unknown or uninitialised column: `sample_id`.
# Extract PFAS matrix (samples x compounds)
Y <- as.matrix(pfas_df[, c("pfos", "pfoa")])

# Center & scale (z-score by column)
X_centered <- X - rowMeans(X, na.rm = TRUE)
sd_X <- rowSds(X, na.rm = TRUE)
X_scaled <- X_centered / sd_X

Y_centered <- scale(Y, center = TRUE, scale = TRUE)  # samples x PFAS

# -----------------------------
# 5. Compute correlations vectorized
# -----------------------------
# Now the multiplication works: (features x samples) %*% (samples x PFAS) -> features x PFAS
cor_mat <- (X_scaled %*% Y_centered) / (ncol(X_scaled) - 1)
rownames(cor_mat) <- rownames(X)
colnames(cor_mat) <- c("PFOS", "PFOA")

# -----------------------------
# 6. Filter significant features
# -----------------------------
# Example: |correlation| > 0.3
sig_threshold <- 0.3
sig_features <- processed[keep_features, ][
  apply(abs(cor_mat), 1, max) > sig_threshold, 
]

# -----------------------------
# 7. Plot histograms safely
# -----------------------------
plot_hist_safe <- function(corr_vec, title) {
  corr_vec <- corr_vec[!is.na(corr_vec)]
  if(length(corr_vec) > 0) {
    hist(corr_vec, main = title, xlab = "Correlation", breaks = 30)
  } else {
    message("No valid correlations to plot for ", title)
  }
}

plot_hist_safe(cor_mat[, "PFOS"], "Correlation with PFOS")
## No valid correlations to plot for Correlation with PFOS
plot_hist_safe(cor_mat[, "PFOA"], "Correlation with PFOA")
## No valid correlations to plot for Correlation with PFOA
# -----------------------------
# 8. Save results
# -----------------------------
write_csv(as.data.frame(cor_mat), "feature_pfas_correlations.csv")
write_csv(sig_features, "significant_features.csv")
